<TITLE> Polls will be transparent: Quader </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 15 (bdnews24.com)  Adviser Ghulam Quader is hopeful that the election on Dec. 29 will be transparent and credible. "No power can disrupt the polls," he said to reporters at the housing and public works ministry. Talking about the implementation of the government's anticorruption initiative, he said, "All things cannot be implemented." "Whether corrupt people will win or not in the upcoming election is for the voters to decide." he commented. He also said the government tried its best, amendments had been made and many laws done away with. "Now, it's up to the voters to select the honest candidate." Talking about reforms Quader said, "The government has made several reforms and has left out from the new list the names of one crore 22 lakh false voters that were included before the last election date." "We are keeping a vigilant eye on the possibility of indiscipline during the election and all possibilities are being assessed." "We have defeated professional alarmists at all stages and we will defeat them again through holding a free and fair election." b
